  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But when Sanballat the Horonite, and Tobiah the servant, the Ammonite, and Geshem the Arabian,.... This third man might be both an Arabian by birth, and governor of some part of Arabia near Judea: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "heard it; of their beginning to build: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "they laughed us to scorn, and despised us; as very silly people, that undertook what they could never perform: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and said; adding threatenings to their scoffs: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "what is this thing that ye do? do ye know what ye are about? have ye any authority to do it? it is unlawful, you will certainly suffer for it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "will ye rebel against the king? the king of Persia; it will be deemed rebellion and treason, and you will be taken up and treated as rebels and traitors; take care what you do, be it at your peril if you proceed. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "will ye rebel against the king? the king of Persia; it will be deemed rebellion and treason, and you will be taken up and treated as rebels and traitors; take care what you do, be it at your peril if you proceed. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "But when Sanballat the Horonite, and Tobiah the servant, the Ammonite, and {h} Geshem the Arabian, heard it, they laughed us to scorn, and despised us, and said, What is this thing that ye do? will ye {i} rebel against the king?",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "But when Sanballat the Horonite, and Tobiah the servant, the Ammonite, and ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{h}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " Geshem the Arabian, heard ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "i",
            "class": "",
            "text": "it",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", they laughed us to scorn, and despised us, and said, What ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "i",
            "class": "",
            "text": "is",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " this thing that ye do? will ye ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{i}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " rebel against the king?",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(h) These were three chief governors under the king of Persia beyond the Euphrates.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(i) Thus the wicked when they will burden the children of God, always lay treason to their charge both because it makes them most odious to the world, and also stirs the hatred of princes against them.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "19, 20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Derision of the Enemy",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
